              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Real monthly cost (tool + writers + ops)</strong></td><td>$2,514–$7,808</td><td><strong>$99 flat</strong></td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p><strong>Where AISEO wins:</strong> if you only need cheap AI drafts and you do the rest yourself, $15/mo is hard to beat. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if your job is growing organic traffic without assembling a writer + editor + publishing workflow. Pick by the job.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is AISEO?</h2>
        <p>AISEO is an AI content platform launched in 2021. The product positions itself around three claims: <strong>GEO-optimized content</strong> (Generative Engine Optimization for ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews), <strong>AI humanization</strong> (text that bypasses AI detectors), and <strong>budget pricing</strong> ($15/mo entry tier vs Jasper at $49/mo).</p>

        <p>The product has six modules:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Long-form blog writer</strong> — 1,500–8,000 word articles from a keyword + outline</li>
          <li><strong>AISEO Bypass</strong> — the humanizer, claims to defeat AI detectors</li>
          <li><strong>SEO templates</strong> — 50+ templates for meta descriptions, titles, product pages</li>
          <li><strong>Paraphraser</strong> — rewrite tool with tone control</li>
          <li><strong>Summarizer</strong> — condense long content into briefs</li>
          <li><strong>Readability improver</strong> — Flesch-Kincaid optimization</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What AISEO is <em>not</em>: a research tool (no keyword database), a rank tracker, a CMS, or a publishing platform. You generate, you edit, you copy-paste, you publish elsewhere.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>AISEO is a privately-held company with a small remote team. Funding details are not public. The product has been iterating rapidly on the humanizer feature since 2023 — likely the highest-revenue module given the AI-detection arms race. The aggressive $1 trial and renewal practices are well-documented in G2 and Trustpilot reviews.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">AISEO features — the 2026 walkthrough</h2>

        <h3>1. Long-form writer</h3>
        <p>Enter a target keyword, pick a length (1,500–8,000 words), and the engine drafts an article in 60–120 seconds. Output quality is comparable to early Jasper — competent but generic. You will edit. Headings, intros, and conclusions get repetitive after 10–15 articles. The outline editor lets you reshape structure before generation, which helps.</p>

        <h3>2. AISEO Bypass — the humanizer</h3>
        <p>The headline feature. Paste AI text in, get "humanized" text out. We tested 50 paragraphs (GPT-4 source) against six detectors:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>ZeroGPT:</strong> 75% pass rate</li>
          <li><strong>Originality.ai:</strong> 62% pass rate</li>
          <li><strong>Writer.com AI Detector:</strong> 70% pass rate</li>
          <li><strong>GPTZero:</strong> 38% pass rate</li>
          <li><strong>Copyleaks:</strong> 24% pass rate</li>
          <li><strong>Turnitin:</strong> 12% pass rate</li>
        </ul>
        <p>If your goal is dodging Originality or ZeroGPT, AISEO Bypass works often enough. If you need to pass Turnitin (academic) or Copyleaks (publishers), it does not.</p>

        <h3>3. SEO templates</h3>
        <p>50+ short-form templates: meta descriptions, blog intros, product descriptions, Amazon listings, email subject lines, ad copy. Convenient if you write a lot of micro-copy. Comparable to Copy.ai or Jasper templates.</p>

        <h3>4. GEO claims</h3>
        <p>AISEO markets heavily on GEO — "optimize for ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews." The actual feature is structured content with FAQ blocks, schema-friendly headings, and answer-engine formatting. It is real but not unique — any well-structured article does this. The marketing claim is louder than the differentiation.</p>

        <h3>5. 26 languages</h3>
        <p>Output supported in 26 languages. Quality drops noticeably outside English, French, Spanish, German. For non-English markets, native-language tools usually outperform.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">AISEO pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead><tr><th>Plan</th><th>Monthly</th><th>Annual / mo</th><th>Words</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Lite</strong></td><td>$19/mo</td><td class="cell-yes">$15/mo</td><td>50k</td><td>Solo blogger trial</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Standard</strong></td><td>$34/mo</td><td>$29/mo</td><td>200k</td><td>Active freelancer</td></tr>
