        <h2 id="verdict">Is AISEO worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For solo bloggers and freelancers: yes, conditionally.</strong> $15/mo annual is a fair price for usable AI drafts. Edit the output, fact-check claims, ignore the GEO marketing. Treat the humanizer as a maybe, not a guarantee.</p>

        <p><strong>For SEO teams: no.</strong> AISEO is a single-purpose draft engine. You will still need Ahrefs ($129/mo), Surfer ($119/mo), editors ($1,800/mo), and a publishing workflow. Total: ~$3,300/mo for a setup that an integrated platform handles for $99–$167.</p>

        <p><strong>For anyone betting on the humanizer: be cautious.</strong> Pass rates vary 12–75% depending on the detector. Detection improves monthly. If your publishing strategy requires consistent bypass, plan for the day the detector wins.</p>

